  <source>Institut Bergonié</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The surgery of breast cancer is responsible for post-operative pain, needing in about 30%
      some morphine consumption; like that, the association of ketamine with general anaesthesia
      may decrease morphine's use and so its adverse effects. The purpose is to evaluate the
      analgesic effect of a receptor NMDA's antagonist ( ketamine)
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
